1
00:00:55,213 --> 00:00:56,763
When people finish their day

2
00:00:57,087 --> 00:00:59,677
and hurry home,

3
00:01:00,370 --> 00:01:01,740
my day starts.

4
00:01:19,605 --> 00:01:22,275
My diner is open from midnight

5
00:01:22,808 --> 00:01:24,218
to seven in the morning.

6
00:01:25,276 --> 00:01:28,146
They call it "Midnight Diner."

7
00:01:33,018 --> 00:01:34,528
Do I even have customers?

8
00:01:35,037 --> 00:01:36,787
More than you would expect.

9
00:01:39,810 --> 00:01:42,703
MIDNIGHT DINER:
TOKYO STORIES

10
00:01:42,703 --> 00:01:48,078
TONTEKI

11
00:01:51,501 --> 00:01:53,341
Once it starts to get cold,

12
00:01:53,795 --> 00:01:57,675
Shigemi knits a new sweater every year.

13
00:02:01,678 --> 00:02:02,548
You're so good.

14
00:02:03,722 --> 00:02:04,812
I'm just used to it.

15
00:02:05,557 --> 00:02:06,927
A gift for your boyfriend?

16
00:02:07,643 --> 00:02:09,561
Boyfriend? Kind of.

17
00:02:09,561 --> 00:02:11,901
To tell you the truth,
she knits one

18
00:02:12,272 --> 00:02:14,272
for a different "boyfriend" each time.

19
00:02:15,126 --> 00:02:17,006
Here is your tonteki.

20
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:19,849
These days it's rare to see

21
00:02:20,298 --> 00:02:22,048
someone knitting in a public place.

22
00:02:23,001 --> 00:02:24,251
You're right about that.

23
00:02:29,039 --> 00:02:29,869
Welcome.

24
00:02:31,102 --> 00:02:32,892
Mr. Ichihara!

25
00:02:33,063 --> 00:02:35,445
Hi, Ms. Suzuki. How are you?

26
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:36,736
Well. Thank you.

27
00:02:43,637 --> 00:02:44,547
Is he your friend?

28
00:02:45,662 --> 00:02:47,872
This is Mr. Ichihara,
an interior designer.

29
00:02:48,151 --> 00:02:50,509
He recently opened his office
in this area.

30
00:02:50,686 --> 00:02:52,806
Ms. Suzuki recommended this joint to me.

31
00:02:54,898 --> 00:02:56,469
Two pork soup combos, please.

32
00:02:56,470 --> 00:02:58,720
- A smaller size for me.
- Sure thing.

33
00:03:00,881 --> 00:03:04,101
This is Ms. Suzuki, a realtor
who helped me find the office.

34
00:03:04,459 --> 00:03:07,879
Thank you for finding
such a great property.

35
00:03:08,312 --> 00:03:10,062
I was just doing my job.

36
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:15,227
Why don't we ask her
to find our condo, too?

37
00:03:15,227 --> 00:03:16,513
That's a good idea.

38
00:03:17,082 --> 00:03:20,302
We are planning to live near my office.
Can you find one for us?

39
00:03:21,141 --> 00:03:22,845
Yes, of course.

40
00:03:39,276 --> 00:03:40,106
Why?

41
00:03:41,872 --> 00:03:42,712
Here.

42
00:03:47,265 --> 00:03:48,725
Don't tell me...

43
00:03:49,870 --> 00:03:51,160
this was for that guy.

44
00:03:51,965 --> 00:03:55,925
Obviously, I'm just a realtor
for Mr. Ichihara.

45
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:59,720
Were you knitting it for a man
who isn't even your boyfriend?

46
00:04:02,309 --> 00:04:04,689
You didn't even know
that he had a girlfriend?

47
00:04:06,025 --> 00:04:08,298
It was very premature.

48
00:04:08,875 --> 00:04:10,587
It's fine. I'm used to it!

49
00:04:24,550 --> 00:04:25,880
Think she'll be okay?

50
00:04:26,171 --> 00:04:27,961
She was so shocked.

51
00:04:29,010 --> 00:04:30,821
Don't worry.

52
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,134
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

53
00:04:33,497 --> 00:04:34,997
Shigemi looks fragile,

54
00:04:35,238 --> 00:04:37,102
but she's resilient.

55
00:04:39,818 --> 00:04:40,704
I was right.

56
00:04:41,004 --> 00:04:43,804
About ten days later...

57
00:04:44,674 --> 00:04:45,514
It's open.

58
00:04:47,511 --> 00:04:48,524
Hello!

59
00:04:49,335 --> 00:04:50,368
Here you go.

60
00:04:50,764 --> 00:04:52,354
Thank you.

61
00:04:53,584 --> 00:04:57,334
He'll make you whatever you want,
so ask for anything.

62
00:04:58,696 --> 00:05:01,259
As long as I have the ingredients for it.

63
00:05:02,059 --> 00:05:04,389
Kurihara, Yoshida and Shirano.

64
00:05:04,563 --> 00:05:06,523
They're younger colleagues of mine.

65
00:05:07,669 --> 00:05:08,773
Did you know, Master?

66
00:05:08,773 --> 00:05:12,406
Kurihara is from Yokkaichi,
and tonteki is his favorite food.

67
00:05:12,632 --> 00:05:15,593
I hear that Yokkaichi
is famous for tonteki.

68
00:05:15,593 --> 00:05:17,582
Yes, the meat has several slits,

69
00:05:17,582 --> 00:05:19,132
and the thick sauce is unique.

70
00:05:20,293 --> 00:05:24,150
My sauce is light,
so I don't know if you'll like it or not.

71
00:05:24,151 --> 00:05:25,201
I'd like to try it.

72
00:05:26,463 --> 00:05:27,854
How about you, Yoshida?

73
00:05:27,855 --> 00:05:32,015
Sorry, I don't eat anything after nine,
so I don't gain weight.

74
00:05:32,016 --> 00:05:32,936
I see.

75
00:05:33,265 --> 00:05:34,315
And you, Shirano?

76
00:05:35,950 --> 00:05:37,530
I will have tonteki, too.

77
00:05:38,353 --> 00:05:40,653
- Then three tontekis, please.
- Got it.

78
00:05:41,857 --> 00:05:44,703
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

79
00:05:57,267 --> 00:05:59,987
Ms. Suzuki, you like to knit?

80
00:06:01,376 --> 00:06:03,456
Ever since I was little.

81
00:06:03,638 --> 00:06:06,688
I like women who can knit.
They look quite feminine.

82
00:06:09,509 --> 00:06:11,509
I'd like to learn it, then.

83
00:06:11,736 --> 00:06:13,996
Ms. Suzuki, can you teach me?

84
00:06:28,348 --> 00:06:29,178
Here you go.

85
00:06:38,191 --> 00:06:39,021
Like it?

86
00:06:43,047 --> 00:06:43,877
I see.

87
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:47,867
Yokkaichi's tonteki goes well with rice.

88
00:06:48,590 --> 00:06:50,010
Yours is perfect for drinks.

89
00:06:53,212 --> 00:06:54,882
Actually, can I have rice?

90
00:06:55,575 --> 00:06:56,415
Sure.

91
00:06:57,585 --> 00:06:59,875
Rice with this?
You'll gain weight for sure.

92
00:07:01,201 --> 00:07:03,781
I guess Shigemi's current love interest...

93
00:07:04,606 --> 00:07:05,896
is this guy.

94
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,190
I'm leaving.

95
00:07:09,923 --> 00:07:10,803
See you tomorrow.

96
00:07:19,318 --> 00:07:20,148
I'm going home.

97
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:33,560
See you tomorrow.

98
00:07:36,304 --> 00:07:38,104
- Kurihara.
- Yes?

99
00:07:39,771 --> 00:07:40,861
For you.

100
00:07:43,157 --> 00:07:43,997
Really?

101
00:07:47,825 --> 00:07:49,437
I hope it's your size.

102
00:08:04,457 --> 00:08:05,367
Perfect.

103
00:08:07,127 --> 00:08:08,417
Can I really have it?

104
00:08:13,218 --> 00:08:15,125
I've wanted a sweater like this.

105
00:08:16,265 --> 00:08:17,305
Thank you so much.

106
00:08:22,309 --> 00:08:25,320
And? What was his reaction?

107
00:08:26,723 --> 00:08:28,632
I think he likes it.

108
00:08:29,608 --> 00:08:32,818
But I don't feel
like it makes us any closer.

109
00:08:32,995 --> 00:08:36,415
Did you tell him how you felt
when you gave it to him?

110
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:44,539
But he accepted the gift.

111
00:08:44,539 --> 00:08:47,669
That means he probably accepted
my feelings, too. Right?

112
00:08:48,078 --> 00:08:49,242
Am I right?

113
00:08:50,805 --> 00:08:54,757
Men wouldn't be excited about a
handmade sweater from someone...

114
00:08:54,757 --> 00:08:56,296
...whom they're not interested in.

115
00:08:56,507 --> 00:08:59,242
But he accepted it.

116
00:08:59,243 --> 00:09:01,453
Which means he accepted her love, right?

117
00:09:01,931 --> 00:09:03,141
Come on.

118
00:09:03,367 --> 00:09:08,104
Knitting a sweater to grab his attention?
You're beating around the bush.

119
00:09:08,104 --> 00:09:10,466
Why don't you just say, "I love you"?

120
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:12,238
You're not a teen anymore.

121
00:09:12,238 --> 00:09:15,939
Not everyone's mentally tough
like you are, Rumi.

122
00:09:15,939 --> 00:09:17,657
It's like fracturing a bone.

123
00:09:17,658 --> 00:09:20,528
Once it heals, that part gets tougher.

124
00:09:21,419 --> 00:09:22,537
What do you mean?

125
00:09:26,147 --> 00:09:26,987
Welcome.

126
00:09:39,118 --> 00:09:41,878
What does Kurihara think about me?

127
00:09:43,390 --> 00:09:45,310
Can you ask him casually?

128
00:09:46,082 --> 00:09:47,082
You want me to ask?

129
00:09:47,769 --> 00:09:50,939
You're the only one I can rely on.

130
00:09:58,863 --> 00:09:59,703
Sure.

131
00:10:00,907 --> 00:10:01,947
I'll ask him.

132
00:10:02,450 --> 00:10:03,490
I appreciate it.

133
00:10:10,667 --> 00:10:12,497
Excuse me, Ms. Suzuki.

134
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:14,400
Yes?

135
00:10:15,672 --> 00:10:16,962
Well...

136
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:20,940
in return for that,

137
00:10:22,501 --> 00:10:24,501
will you teach me how to knit?

138
00:10:25,364 --> 00:10:26,324
What?

139
00:10:28,143 --> 00:10:29,733
I'd like to knit a scarf.

140
00:10:31,135 --> 00:10:32,095
Okay, but...

141
00:10:32,772 --> 00:10:34,112
Is it a gift for someone?

142
00:10:37,023 --> 00:10:38,943
Is it difficult to knit a scarf?

143
00:10:39,575 --> 00:10:41,115
Not at all. Don't worry.

144
00:10:41,494 --> 00:10:43,244
The important thing is your heart.

145
00:10:43,654 --> 00:10:46,234
She will be so happy
if you give it to her.

146
00:10:47,667 --> 00:10:48,689
Here you go.

147
00:10:48,689 --> 00:10:51,333
- Enjoy the meal.
- Yes.

148
00:10:52,182 --> 00:10:55,012
I see. A scarf, huh?

149
00:10:55,926 --> 00:10:57,096
How old is she?

150
00:10:58,715 --> 00:11:01,185
She is about your age.

151
00:11:10,602 --> 00:11:13,062
I'm so clumsy.

152
00:11:15,210 --> 00:11:17,130
I think you're good with your hands.

153
00:11:20,309 --> 00:11:21,979
When I was in elementary school,

154
00:11:22,502 --> 00:11:26,172
I wrote in an essay
that my favorite food is tonteki.

155
00:11:27,368 --> 00:11:32,658
So, a boy I liked started calling me
"Pig Girl who likes tonteki."

156
00:11:33,293 --> 00:11:34,663
I was overweight back then.

157
00:11:39,184 --> 00:11:41,173
I have low self esteem.

158
00:11:41,174 --> 00:11:44,644
Whenever I like someone,
I knit a sweater, or a scarf.

159
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:48,290
In most cases,
I don't even give it to him.

160
00:11:55,271 --> 00:11:56,771
By the way, did you ask him?

161
00:11:57,190 --> 00:11:58,020
What?

162
00:11:59,365 --> 00:12:01,190
Oh! Right.

163
00:12:04,402 --> 00:12:05,612
I think...

164
00:12:07,325 --> 00:12:09,375
Kurihara doesn't like...

165
00:12:10,036 --> 00:12:13,866
the color of the sweater
you gave him.

166
00:12:15,604 --> 00:12:16,524
But...

167
00:12:17,514 --> 00:12:19,054
he wears it at home.

168
00:12:20,467 --> 00:12:21,717
He's a nice guy.

169
00:12:22,966 --> 00:12:26,348
So, he couldn't tell you
that it wasn't his favorite color.

170
00:12:26,348 --> 00:12:28,148
Is that right?

171
00:12:28,536 --> 00:12:31,376
He should have told me that.
I wouldn't be hurt.

172
00:12:32,572 --> 00:12:35,152
What is his favorite color, then?

173
00:12:37,272 --> 00:12:39,902
I see. The issue was the color, huh?

174
00:12:40,608 --> 00:12:41,978
How about this one?

175
00:12:45,947 --> 00:12:46,777
Or...

176
00:12:47,532 --> 00:12:49,492
maybe a brighter color?

177
00:12:53,293 --> 00:12:54,123
Welcome.

178
00:12:58,585 --> 00:13:00,885
This is your first time coming alone.

179
00:13:01,979 --> 00:13:02,819
Right.

180
00:13:05,654 --> 00:13:08,052
Have you finished the scarf?

181
00:13:15,351 --> 00:13:17,641
I lied about that.

182
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:20,310
What?

183
00:13:21,190 --> 00:13:23,437
- I'm leaving.
- See you tomorrow.

184
00:13:29,949 --> 00:13:31,949
Hey, Shirano. Do you have a moment?

185
00:13:36,414 --> 00:13:38,334
I've been going out with Yoshida.

186
00:13:38,705 --> 00:13:39,705
Oh really?

187
00:13:41,085 --> 00:13:41,965
And...

188
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:46,210
Ms. Suzuki gave this to me.

189
00:13:49,677 --> 00:13:53,347
Yoshida ripped it
to see how strong it was.

190
00:13:55,870 --> 00:13:57,040
Women are nasty.

191
00:14:01,778 --> 00:14:02,698
So...

192
00:14:03,775 --> 00:14:06,445
Can you throw it away for me?

193
00:14:12,408 --> 00:14:13,238
Really?

194
00:14:13,945 --> 00:14:14,865
Thank you so much.

195
00:14:15,594 --> 00:14:19,383
A handmade sweater
carries so much emotion.

196
00:14:20,249 --> 00:14:21,379
I can't do it myself.

197
00:14:32,521 --> 00:14:33,521
What are you doing?

198
00:14:34,973 --> 00:14:35,893
It's just trash.

199
00:14:39,435 --> 00:14:41,565
I'm disappointed in myself.

200
00:14:45,358 --> 00:14:47,188
Ms. Suzuki confided in me.

201
00:14:48,945 --> 00:14:51,575
I knew I should tell her the truth,

202
00:14:54,117 --> 00:14:55,197
but I couldn't.

203
00:14:58,289 --> 00:14:59,119
She's...

204
00:15:00,526 --> 00:15:03,776
knitting another sweater for Kurihara.

205
00:15:05,712 --> 00:15:06,962
I feel so bad.

206
00:15:09,429 --> 00:15:10,559
Then...

207
00:15:11,926 --> 00:15:13,756
the reason for making a scarf was...

208
00:15:16,685 --> 00:15:19,395
I wanted to repair the sweater myself.

209
00:15:20,226 --> 00:15:22,136
That's why I learned how to knit.

210
00:15:24,467 --> 00:15:27,387
I know she didn't knit it for me, but...

211
00:15:29,506 --> 00:15:31,836
it's made with Ms. Suzuki's love.

212
00:15:35,416 --> 00:15:36,326
What now?

213
00:15:37,326 --> 00:15:38,286
Will you...

214
00:15:38,867 --> 00:15:40,737
stick to the lie?

215
00:15:54,202 --> 00:15:55,032
Welcome.

216
00:15:57,179 --> 00:15:58,179
Ms. Suzuki?

217
00:15:59,140 --> 00:16:01,810
Kurihara.
Why are you here?

218
00:16:02,356 --> 00:16:05,196
Shirano asked me to come here
and talk to him.

219
00:16:05,471 --> 00:16:06,721
He asked me to come, too.

220
00:16:09,025 --> 00:16:10,235
Would you like to sit?

221
00:16:23,776 --> 00:16:25,566
Why are you wearing that?

222
00:16:26,834 --> 00:16:28,344
Kurihara gave it to me.

223
00:16:30,616 --> 00:16:33,286
Kurihara is dating Yoshida.

224
00:16:33,424 --> 00:16:34,594
Why are you...?

225
00:16:42,717 --> 00:16:44,267
Is that so?

226
00:16:44,953 --> 00:16:46,663
Come on, Kurihara.

227
00:16:47,089 --> 00:16:50,469
You should have told me that.

228
00:17:03,101 --> 00:17:04,021
Ms. Suzuki.

229
00:17:06,374 --> 00:17:07,374
What can I say?

230
00:17:09,168 --> 00:17:10,088
I'm sorry.

231
00:17:17,272 --> 00:17:18,312
Ms. Shigemi!

232
00:17:21,542 --> 00:17:22,672
This sweater...

233
00:17:23,766 --> 00:17:25,136
is warm...

234
00:17:26,060 --> 00:17:27,140
and very comfy.

235
00:17:28,813 --> 00:17:29,863
I really like it.

236
00:17:33,121 --> 00:17:34,281
So what?

237
00:17:37,384 --> 00:17:38,304
So...

238
00:17:40,324 --> 00:17:42,664
I don't care about the sweater anymore!

239
00:17:46,267 --> 00:17:48,147
Shigemi or Shirano

240
00:17:48,666 --> 00:17:51,836
didn't come back for a while after that.

241
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:11,650
Come in. This way.

242
00:18:15,276 --> 00:18:17,186
It's bigger than I expected.

243
00:18:18,237 --> 00:18:20,157
We can have a dining table here.

244
00:18:21,741 --> 00:18:23,451
The TV would be there?

245
00:18:25,703 --> 00:18:29,240
- It's perfect for two of us, but...
- What?

246
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:32,543
I'm thinking about a kid.

247
00:18:52,813 --> 00:18:54,363
Have you been drinking alone?

248
00:18:59,862 --> 00:19:02,282
I quit knitting.

249
00:19:05,422 --> 00:19:06,462
I realized that...

250
00:19:06,994 --> 00:19:08,726
it's strange to give

251
00:19:08,727 --> 00:19:12,147
a handmade sweater to someone
I'm not even dating.

252
00:19:13,042 --> 00:19:14,792
It was silly of me to get excited.

253
00:19:15,492 --> 00:19:17,282
I'm such an idiot.

254
00:19:19,736 --> 00:19:20,786
I don't know.

255
00:19:24,167 --> 00:19:25,207
The other day...

256
00:19:26,378 --> 00:19:27,418
Shirano...

257
00:19:28,054 --> 00:19:29,814
came here by himself.

258
00:19:32,116 --> 00:19:33,326
He sat there...

259
00:19:34,224 --> 00:19:36,434
and was repairing the sweater.

260
00:19:37,931 --> 00:19:39,141
Right up here...

261
00:19:39,941 --> 00:19:41,231
there was a hole.

262
00:19:44,579 --> 00:19:46,119
He was not good at knitting.

263
00:19:46,872 --> 00:19:48,282
And I felt bad for him.

264
00:19:50,037 --> 00:19:52,827
He said,
"it's made with Ms. Suzuki's love."

265
00:19:53,826 --> 00:19:55,706
He worked so hard to fix it.

266
00:20:16,897 --> 00:20:18,607
That can't be true.

267
00:20:23,571 --> 00:20:24,991
What is this feeling?

268
00:20:25,948 --> 00:20:27,318
What...

269
00:20:28,078 --> 00:20:29,498
is this feeling?

270
00:20:29,844 --> 00:20:31,579
What is this feeling?

271
00:20:31,579 --> 00:20:34,594
What is this feeling?

272
00:20:34,594 --> 00:20:35,732
Shigemi?

273
00:20:36,039 --> 00:20:36,959
Are you okay?

274
00:20:42,629 --> 00:20:44,839
What the hell is this feeling?

275
00:21:00,138 --> 00:21:01,348
Are you okay?

276
00:21:02,985 --> 00:21:04,115
Ms. Suzuki?

277
00:21:11,494 --> 00:21:12,624
Shirano...

278
